      "message": "Correct me if I'm wrong but the way I was understanding it was that in this case \"/unknown\" is a parent node so the child list-node has been left empty. So \"/unknown/child\" would be valid as long as \"child\" exists. Since an invalid XPath has been entered for this usage I used CpsPathException. Is there a better Exception I can use instead?",
